		<div id="article-correspondences" class="correspondences correspondences-collapsed">
								<div class="block-correspondence" id="2988">
		<blockquote class="quote-2">
			<p>Thank you for printing Charles Goodrich&rsquo;s &ldquo;<a href="/article/1584/">Fathering the Night</a>&rdquo; [February 1995]. My five-month-old son now sleeps until 5 or even 6 <span class="smallcaps">A.M.</span>, but bedtime anxiety is still an uneasy memory. I thought those demons &mdash; the airless nursery, the man sneaking up the stairs, the burning house &mdash; were just my unique form of postpartum depression. Thanks for clearing it up for me.</p>
							<p class="quote-2-author">Lisa Stopoulos-Alexander<br>Rockford, Illinois</p>
					</blockquote>
	</div>

